      <mj-column width="100%">
        <mj-text padding-bottom="0px">
          <h2 style="font-weight: bold">Process</h2>
          <p><a href="https://www.protocol.com/google-open-source-istio">Will Google donate open-source Istio to a foundation</a><br />
            &rdquo;&lsquo;It&rsquo;s a real problem,&rsquo; said Nicolas Chaillan, chief software officer for the U.S. Air Force, which has made a sizable bet on Istio as a key component of its cloud strategy. &lsquo;I reached out to Google [after Kubecon] to say that if we don&rsquo;t get Istio within the CNCF, we&rsquo;ll have to drop it.&lsquo;&rdquo;</p>

          <p><a href="https://www.zdnet.com/article/the-linux-foundation-identifies-the-most-important-open-source-software-components-and-their-problems/">The Linux Foundation identifies most important open-source software components and their problems</a><br />
            &ldquo;In its latest study, the Linux Foundation&rsquo;s Core Infrastructure Initiative discovered just how prevalent open-source components are in all software and their shared problems and vulnerabilities.&rdquo;</p>

          <p><a href="https://logz.io/freeshirt/?utm_source=podcast&amp;utm_medium=devopish&amp;utm_campaign=freeshirt">Open Source-based Cloud Observability</a><br />
            If you are like many of your friends in DevOps, you might prefer using open source solutions. Logz.io&rsquo;s <a href="https://logz.io/freeshirt/?utm_source=podcast&amp;utm_medium=devopish&amp;utm_campaign=freeshirt">cloud observability platform</a> is designed to help deliver the open source experience you love, at the scale you need. Log management and Cloud SIEM based on ELK, and Infrastructure monitoring based on Grafana. All on one unified platform to help you correlate quickly between logs and metrics. Sign up for a <a href="https://logz.io/freeshirt/?utm_source=podcast&amp;utm_medium=devopish&amp;utm_campaign=freeshirt">free trial today</a> and receive a Logz.io t-shirt! <em>SPONSORED</em></p>

          <p><a href="https://verraes.net/2020/01/wall-of-technical-debt/">The Wall of Technical Debt</a><br />
            &ldquo;Or perhaps fixing it isn&rsquo;t worth it? That&rsquo;s not a matter of aesthetics or opinion anymore. It&rsquo;s a matter of empirically collected metrics. Congratulations, you&rsquo;re negotiating tradeoffs as a team.&rdquo;</p>

          <p><a href="https://siliconangle.com/2020/02/20/hp-adopts-limited-duration-shareholder-rights-plan-fend-off-xerox-takeover-attempt/">HP adopts limited shareholder rights plan to fend off Xerox takeover attempt</a><br />
            The HP/Xerox saga continues. I&rsquo;m starting to wonder when Xerox runs out of clock on this. There has to be some critical reason(s) Xerox&rsquo;s board sees this as it&rsquo;s future. Eventually, investors are going to want this work to pay off. If it never materializes, which seems more and more likely, then what Xerox?</p>

          <p><a href="https://opensource.com/article/20/2/product-marketing-open-source-project">3 steps for product marketing your open source project</a><br />
            &ldquo;How do I market my open source XYZ?&rdquo; is a question I get at least once a week. At some point, I&rsquo;ll write a book about it. But, for now, I&rsquo;m still trying to figure it out. But, the one thing I tell folks is to be consistent and authentic. This builds trust. Everything in open source is based on a degree of trust.</p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
