    <mj-section>
      <mj-column width="100%">
        <mj-text padding-bottom="0px">
          <h2 style="font-weight: bold">Tools</h2>
          <p><a href="https://thenewstack.io/kubernetes-performance-troublespots-airbnbs-take/">Kubernetes Performance Trouble Spots: Airbnb&rsquo;s Take</a><br />
            Running thousands of pods in prod leads to a number of ways performance inconsistencies could pop up.</p>

          <p><a href="https://www.jeffgeerling.com/blog/2020/kubernetes-collection-ansible">The Kubernetes Collection for Ansible</a><br />
            Jeff Geerling has made significant strides in getting an Ansible collection of Kubernetes tools together. If you&rsquo;re doing templating with Ansible, need to use Ansible in CI to mangle your Kubernetes objects, or something else with Ansible give it a look.</p>

          <p><a href="https://www.lastweekinaws.com/podcast/screaming-in-the-cloud/the-staying-power-of-kubernetes-with-kelsey-hightower/">The Staying Power of Kubernetes with Kelsey Hightower</a><br />
            Kelsey answers a &ldquo;grumpy Unix sysadmin&rsquo;s&rdquo; questions. Because, &ldquo;It&rsquo;s not like there&rsquo;s a second kind of Unix sysadmin you&rsquo;re ever going to encounter.&rdquo;</p>

          <p><a href="https://www.datadoghq.com/dg/monitor/kubernetes-monitoring-benefits/?utm_source=Advertisement&amp;utm_medium=Advertisement&amp;utm_campaign=DevOpsish-Newsletter01&amp;utm_content=Kubernetes">Dynamic Kubernetes Monitoring</a><br />
            Monitor and manage your dynamic Kubernetes container fleet with Datadog. Use the Container Map to group, filter, and explore your containers, and the Live Container view to investigate the metrics and processes of individual containers. Try Datadog in your environment with a free 14-day trial. <em>SPONSORED</em></p>

          <p><a href="https://towardsdatascience.com/stop-making-data-scientists-manage-kubernetes-clusters-53c3b584cb08">Stop making data scientists manage Kubernetes clusters</a><br />
            The case for a career trajectory that has job titles like, Machine learning infrastructure engineer, Data science platform engineer, and ML production engineer. I could definitely get down with this line of work.</p>

          <p><a href="https://devopsish.com/pdf/census_ii_vulnerabilities_in_the_core.pdf">Census II</a><br />
            &ldquo;Census II identifies the most commonly used free and open source software (FOSS) components in production applications and begins to examine them for potential vulnerabilities, which can inform actions to sustain the long-term security and health of FOSS.&rdquo; I&rsquo;m actually a little surprised at this list. I figured there would be things like NTP and DNS knowledge.</p>

          <p><a href="https://www.techradar.com/news/cobol-remains-an-important-programming-priority">COBOL stays top of mind for businesses in 2020</a><br />
            COBOL is still going strong after all these years. These systems aren&rsquo;t going anywhere because they were built to last. Figuring out the best abstraction points will be critical in the future. Understanding the design of these systems and the way your systems interface with them will be increasingly important.</p>

          <p><a href="http://highscalability.com/blog/2020/2/19/moores-law-is-not-ending-soon-and-the-reason-may-surprise-yo.html">Moore&rsquo;s Law is not Ending Soon and the Reason May Surprise You</a><br />
            Long live Moore&rsquo;s Law!</p>

          <p><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/pulse/vmware-kubernetes-epic-fail-flight-jay-valentine/">VMware Kubernetes ‚Äì Epic Fail In Flight</a><br />
            One person&rsquo;s view on how VMware&rsquo;s Kubernetes play could be doomed before it even gets off the ground.</p>

          <p><a href="https://understandlegacycode.com/blog/5-arguments-to-make-managers-care-about-technical-debt/">5 arguments to make managers care about technical debt</a><br />
            Debt is a tool. But, managing that debt is vital. Letting debt manage you leads to horrible things. I&rsquo;m talking about money here but, your org&rsquo;s codebases might be old enough to be at this level of impact too. But, much like you had to learn some money management terms to navigate the financial world, you&rsquo;ll have to adopt new language to get management to understand the need to manage this tech debt sooner rather than later.</p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
